body: The PR description/test plan mentions fixing auto-install on Windows, but `installSignalCli()` currently returns "not supported on Windows yet" in this same file. Please align the PR description/test plan with the current behavior (macOS/Linux only), or update the implementation to actually support Windows installs.

body: Within the new fallback predicates, `asset.name.toLowerCase()` is computed multiple times per asset. Consider storing the lowercased name in a local variable inside the callback to improve readability and avoid repeated string allocations.
@copilot open a new pull request to apply changes based on [this feedback](https://github.com/clawdbot/clawdbot/pull/2204#discussion_r2727366451)

[P1] Windows fallback can still select `*-windows-native.tar.gz`, which can’t run under WSL/Linux.

In the `win32` branch, the fallback only excludes `linux-native`, but not Windows native builds. If the release includes `signal-cli-*-windows-native.tar.gz` and no `windows|win` match triggers first, the fallback could select it and later fail on Linux/WSL. Consider mirroring the macOS exclusion by filtering out `windows-native` (or broader `windows` native identifiers) in the fallback selection as well.
